  <Section title="About me" id="about-me">
    <p class="mt-4 leading-loose">
      I am a Ph.D. student in Electrical Engineering at the University of Florida, working in the <Link href="https://focus.ece.ufl.edu/">Focus Lab</Link> under
      the guidance of <Link href="https://www.ece.ufl.edu/people/faculty/sanjeev-j-koppal/">Prof. Dr. Sanjeev Koppal</Link>. My current research focuses on collision prediction, specifically exploring variable temporal resolution to improve
      prediction accuracy and effectiveness. My academic interests lie in computer vision, robotics, and embedded systems, with a strong emphasis on integrating
      these technologies to develop innovative solutions in autonomous systems.
    </p>

